    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-11T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-11T14:00:00-05:00" n="290"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.33/445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-11T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 11, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 12—2:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1758. Foreign Office has received telegram summarizing <hi rend="italic"
                        >aide-mémoire</hi> along the lines of Department’s 1166, November 4, 10
                        p.m.<note n="83" xml:id="d290fn83">Telegram No. 1166 not printed; for <hi
                            rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>, see <hi rend="italic"
                        >supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>It states that the two tankers are already in the inner harbor and the cargo ship
                        <hi rend="italic">Bessel</hi> also will be placed there.</p>
                <p>Department’s 888, September 18, 3 p.m.<note n="84" xml:id="d290fn84">Not
                        printed.</note> Total naval petroleum stocks as of October 10 were 5,799
                    tons fuel oil and 580 tons gas oil divided among <hi rend="italic">Ferrol,
                        Cádiz, Cartagena, Palma, Mahon, Seller, Crucero, Canarias</hi> and the
                    remaining vessels of the Spanish Fleet.</p>
                <p>A later statement of navy stocks is being prepared. A statement of military
                    stocks has also been requested of the military.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
